SSH Publisher:- 

Steps to follow to use SSH Publisher in Jenkins Pipeline.

Change the ownership of remote directory

sudo chown -R owner:group dirname

set the password for the remote user.

allow the user sudo access i.e. add the user in visudo file

In Jenkins under "configure system" under "Publish over SSH" click on "ADD" and then "Name=any name of server", "Hostname= IP of Remote Server"

"Username= Remote server user name" "Remote Directory= Mention the directroy where you want to copy files from jenkins to remote server if not mentioned 

it will take the user's home directory".

Click on "Advanced" Checkbox "Use password authentication, or use a different key" and under "Passphrase / Password" mention the password of the remote server's user.

Lastly Click on Test Configuration it will promt SUCCESS.  
